 <p rend="centre">Translation<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>                    
<p>Waterbuffalo eating indian corn drowned by inundation   nose below water to within an inch of his eye.</p> 
<table>
    <row>
        <cell rend="centre" cols="3"><hi rend="underline">Consecutive seconds</hi></cell>
    </row>
    <row>
        <cell rend="left"> Underwater</cell>
        <cell/>
        <cell rend="left">above</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
        <cell>10</cell>
        <cell/>
        <cell>15</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
        <cell>15</cell>
        <cell/>
        <cell>17</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
        <cell>20</cell>
        <cell/>
        <cell>15</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
        <cell rend="borderBottom">15</cell>
        <cell/>
        <cell rend="borderBottom">10</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
        <cell>60</cell>
        <cell>Men went away</cell>
        <cell>57</cell>
    </row>
</table>

<p>In 1 min 57 sec he was 1 min under water.</p>
<p>corn is under water two months<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>That which shews above the surface is eagerly eaten by the cows and donkeys.</p>
<p>The land shelves down gradually so that the Buffalo who had the longest nose or who could hold his breath longest would get most food. In a time of starvation, as when all their land is under water this would be all important</p> 
                    <p><hi rend="italic">[</hi>Ennery Esq<hi rend="italic">]</hi></p>
